<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Ruatha:
[B][i]Some of the perhaps many unknowns we need to investigate to understand actual weapon damage over time is:

(a) how str bonus is calculated.

Do you get the same bonus on any weapon? 2H or 1H, high or low dmg weapon?[/i]

It can't be a static amount.  It's got to be a percentage.

I think it was 32nd level that my max non-crit damage was exactly 3 times the damage rating on the weapon.  May have been 33rd.  But it was one of the two.  Let's say it was 32nd.

At 32nd, then, I was hitting for a max non-crit damage of 57 with my LotW, and I was hitting for a max non-crit damage of 18 with my 1-handers (all of which were DMG 6).  When I went up a level, I started hitting for 60 points with the LotW, which is a 3 point increase.  However, I only went up 1 point with my 1-handers.  And on some levels I don't see an increase at all with the 1-handers.

Ruatha
[/B][/QUOTE]

