<IFRAME FRAMEBORDER=1 ALIGN=CENTER width=100% HEIGHT=200 SCROLLING=YES SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/Forum21/HTML/001988.html">
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#000050"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#FFFFFF" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Surutca Eagleeye</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Sorry to start these up again but I just have to know  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/smile.gif"><P>I therefore bumb to postings I have made deep down under other topics:<P>FIRST POSTING<P>Some of the perhaps many unknowns we need to investigate to understand actual weapon damage over time is:<P>(a) how str bonus is calculated.<P>Do you get the same bonus on any weapon? 2H or 1H, high or low dmg weapon?<P>I have to go home to check this one <P>And how exactly does it relate to your str?<P>(b) how your below max hits are calculated<P>If its fixed numbers as assumed in the 3 dmg example above then it favors the faster 1H weapons all other things being equal. If its percentages of the normal max damage it dosent matter.<P>(c) how critical hits are calculated<P>I assume its 2 x base dmg (before str bonus) + str bonus.<P>As opposed to 2 x (base dmg +str bonus)<P>Your maximum base dmg being 2 x the weapon damage.<P><BR>Actually we should be able to figure these things out if we just collect diffent players dmg figures at different levels with different weapons and str stats. The only problem is that you normally dont play enough different combos yourself at any given level to figure it out.<P>Surutca Eagleeye<P>SECOND POSTING<P>Come on you high level guys. You can do better than this  simulation and magic number crap.<P>All we need to know is:<P>(a) Is the str bonus a fixed number or a percentage of the weapon dmg (or some combo formula).<P>If its a fixed number the simple dmg/dly ratio will tend to favor the higher dmg 2H when compared to actual in game damage at higher levels.<P>If its a percentage the simple dmg/dly should be ok.<P>This can not be very hard to find out for all you high str warriors with weapons of both types <P>(b) Is lower than max hits a percentage of your ordinary hits (before or after str nonus) or fixed low numbers (or a combo formula)?<P>If its a straight percentage the in game feeling that dual 1H is better than 2H at higher levels has NOTHING to do with the average hit vs max hit argument.<P><BR>I will be waiting for the answers <P>BTW from a mathematical point of wiev there is nothing strange in the fact that dual 1H gets better and better compared to 2H as you raise in levels because of the simple fact that when you use dual 1H there is 2 percentage increases that raise as you level (chance for dubble attack and chance of dual) whereas the 2H warrior only get one percentage increase (chance for dubble attack) not to mention the chance of dubble dual  Therefore the damage courves of a dual 1H warrior will raise faster than that of a 2H warrior and most likely pass it if we for the sake of argument assume that they both stick to 1 weapon throughout their life. It could for that matter be Dual FS longswords vs. FS 2Hander.<P>Therefore if we assume that the simple dmg/dly gap between 1H and 2H is the same for all levels of weapons dual 1H will catch up to 2H. Whether or not it passes depends on the actual dmg/dly difference and thus on the available weapon selection in game.<P>Surutca Eagleeye<P><BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Ruatha</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica"><I>Some of the perhaps many unknowns we need to investigate to understand actual weapon damage over time is:<P>(a) how str bonus is calculated.<P>Do you get the same bonus on any weapon? 2H or 1H, high or low dmg weapon?</I><P>It can't be a static amount.  It's got to be a percentage.<P>I think it was 32nd level that my max non-crit damage was exactly 3 times the damage rating on the weapon.  May have been 33rd.  But it was one of the two.  Let's say it was 32nd.<P>At 32nd, then, I was hitting for a max non-crit damage of 57 with my LotW, and I was hitting for a max non-crit damage of 18 with my 1-handers (all of which were DMG 6).  When I went up a level, I started hitting for 60 points with the LotW, which is a 3 point increase.  However, I only went up 1 point with my 1-handers.  And on some levels I don't see an increase at all with the 1-handers.<P>Ruatha<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Kailyn of Povar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Here is what I have found in getting to 50th.<P>The strength bonus is doubled on 2H weapons when compaired to 1h. That was posted by Verant some time long ago, or perhaps it was a change made in an early patch, I dont recall.<P>Stregth Bonus is a percentage of weapon damage. Max hits will tend to be in the range of 4 to 5 times base damge (max hit with a Ykesha is 42 (8/24), Ex Ax 100 (25/50), dont know what it is with the Mith 2H). My mode with the Mith 2H is 50.<P>2H vs 1h is entirely dependent on the weapons you are using. Using the released formulas and my personal skills (200 Duel Weild, 205 Double attack) on average I will get 1.51 attacks around with 2h and 2.14 with 2 1h weapons. YOu can now take the efficancy your weapons and see which comes out better. For figureing out 2 1h weapons which are different use 1.51*efficancy for the primary and 0.63*efficancy for the second weappon. For 2h weapons use 1.51* efficany. This is based on a 50th level charicter.<P>Criticals seem to be based on the following: minimum hit is 2x damage +1. There is a bonus factor of 0-7 (or 8 this is off the top of my head). The formula for the extra damage seems to be (level-12)/5. <P>------------------<BR>Kailyn Longstride<BR>50th Warrior, Povar<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Shalindrea</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I don't think the formula for extra crit dmg is (level-12)/5.<BR>At lvl 42 the bonus was +5 and it is now +6 at lvl 43.<BR>I don't know at what lvl warriors get +7.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
